-- Bahrain Says One Policeman Injured in Attack in Shiite Village
-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 2012-09-11T11:18:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-11/bahrain-says-one-policeman-injured-in-attack-in-shiite-village.html
One policeman was injured after a
group of people attacked his car with Molotov bombs and Iron
rods in al-Dair village yesterday, the country’s Information
Affairs Authority said in an e-mailed statement today.  The policeman is in hospital in a “critical condition”
and the police are searching for the attackers, the statement
said. Al-Dair is about 15 kilometers north of the capital
Manama.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wael Mahdi in Manama at 
 wmahdi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  